Here is the full **testsmells.org 19-smell catalog** audit of `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs`, with integration-test calibration applied.

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell Count | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| **High** | 2 | 2 |
| **Medium** | 2 | 2 |
| Low | 0 | 0 |
| **Total** | **4** | **6 (of 8)** |

**Overall verdict:** The suite is mostly well-structured — clear AAA layout, proper `[TestInitialize]`/`[TestCleanup]` lifecycle, in-memory SQLite for isolation, and good descriptive naming. Four smells need attention, two of which are High.

---

## High-Severity Findings

### 1. Conditional Test Logic · `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` (line 101)

```csharp
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

**Problem:** The `if/else` means only one branch ever executes per run. If the production code changes which type is returned, one assertion path silently becomes dead code — a hidden testing gap.

**Fix:** Split into two explicit tests, each arranging the specific precondition:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_StandardUser_ReturnsName()
{
    _repository.Insert(new User("eve@example.com", "Eve"));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_PremiumUser_HasPositiveDiscount()
{
    _repository.Insert(new PremiumUser("eve@example.com", "Eve", discountRate: 0.1m));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com") as PremiumUser;

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0);
}
```

---

### 2. Unknown Test (Assertion-Free) · `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` (line 113)

```csharp
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }
    // ← no assertion
}
```

**Problem:** This test passes even if every insert silently fails (e.g., a no-op stub). The name implies a "does-not-throw" intent, but MSTest marks any non-throwing method as green regardless — there is zero verification.

**Fix:** Assert the observable outcome:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_AllRecordsPersisted()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }

    var users = _repository.ListAll();
    Assert.AreEqual(100, users.Count);
}
```

---

## Medium-Severity Findings

### 3. Sleepy Test · `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` (line 87)

```csharp
Thread.Sleep(3000);
```

**Problem:** A hard-coded 3-second sleep makes this test slow and non-deterministic. On a loaded CI machine the delay may not be long enough; locally it wastes time.

**Integration calibration:** Integration tests sometimes need to wait for async side-effects, but `Thread.Sleep` is still the wrong mechanism. Severity is kept at **Medium** (downgraded from High) because this is an integration suite, but it should still be fixed.

**Fix:** Poll with a timeout instead:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay()
{
    var user = new User("dave@example.com", "Dave");
    _repository.Insert(user);

    var timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5);
    var interval = TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100);
    var sw = Stopwatch.StartNew();

    while (sw.Elapsed < timeout)
    {
        if (_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
            return; // success
        await Task.Delay(interval);
    }

    Assert.Fail("Notification was not sent within the timeout period.");
}
```

---

### 4. Assertion Roulette · `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` (line 35)

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
```

**Problem:** Four assertions, none with a message. When one fails in CI, the stack trace shows a line number but the failure reason requires reading source — slows diagnosis.

**Fix:** Add discriminating messages:

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Auto-generated Id should be positive");
```

---

## Smells Scanned — No Issues Found (15 of 19)

| # | Smell (testsmells.org name) | Status |
|---|---|---|
| 2 | **Mystery Guest** | ✅ Clean — in-memory SQLite; no external files/services |
| 5 | **Eager Test** | ✅ Clean — no test calls 4+ distinct production methods |
| 6 | **Magic Number Test** | ✅ Clean — literals (3, 10, 100) are self-documenting from context |
| 7 | **Sensitive Equality** | ✅ Clean — no `ToString()` in assertions |
| 8 | **Exception Handling** | ✅ Clean — no `try`/`catch` in tests |
| 9 | **General Fixture** | ✅ Clean — both `_connection` and `_repository` used by every test |
| 10 | **Ignored Test** | ✅ Clean — no skipped/disabled tests |
| 11 | **Duplicate Assert** | ✅ Clean — no repeated identical assertions |
| 12 | **Lazy Test** | ✅ Clean — each test targets a distinct operation |
| 13 | **Constructor Initialization** | ✅ Clean — uses `[TestInitialize]`, not a constructor |
| 14 | **Default Test** | ✅ Clean — class name is descriptive, not scaffolded |
| 15 | **Redundant Print** | ✅ Clean — no `Console.WriteLine` artifacts |
| 16 | **Redundant Assertion** | ✅ Clean — no always-true tautologies |
| 17 | **Resource Optimism** | ✅ Clean — no assumptions about external resources |
| 18 | **Empty Test** | ✅ Clean — all tests contain executable statements |

---

## Positive Observations

- **Proper lifecycle management** — `[TestInitialize]`/`[TestCleanup]` with in-memory SQLite gives full test isolation with no shared state leaking between tests.
- **`sealed` test class** — prevents accidental inheritance hierarchies.
- **Descriptive `Method_Scenario` naming** — consistent across 7 of 8 tests.
- **Concurrency test** — `InsertUser_ConcurrentInserts_MaintainsIntegrity` is a well-designed stress test with a clear assertion.
- **No over-mocking** — tests exercise the real repository against a real (in-memory) database, appropriate for integration scope.

---

## Prioritized Remediation

| Priority | Smell | Fix Effort | Impact |
|----------|-------|-----------|--------|
| 🔴 1 | **Unknown Test** (`BulkInsert`) | ~2 min | Eliminates false-pass risk |
| 🔴 2 | **Conditional Test Logic** (`GetUser`) | ~5 min | Removes hidden dead-test-path |
| 🟡 3 | **Sleepy Test** (`NotifyOnInsert`) | ~10 min | Faster suite, no flaky timing |
| 🟡 4 | **Assertion Roulette** (`InsertUser`) | ~2 min | Better CI failure diagnostics |

Fix #1 and #2 first — they are the tests most likely to give your team **false confidence**.
